cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on relation extraction from clinical texts using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as kernel methods and classification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for automatic feature learning, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information retrieval and classification, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
